    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flowing floor-length robes with wide sleeves, made of silk or similar material. These are worn by judges while sitting at the bench in courts of law in the United States and elsewhere. Judicial robes in the United States are usually black but may vary in slight detail, as there is no official source or design, in the United Kingdom there exist color variations based on the court in which the judicant sits.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
